cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.DM 

The paper deals with the concept of randomness and compression rate, which are closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). It also discusses the notion of dimension, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and topology (cs.LO). Finally, the paper presents equivalent characterizations of the partial randomness of an r.e. real, which involves the use of computable, increasing sequences of rationals, suggesting a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
